d by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born about 1295, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She married Henry Pettit in 1322, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1295–Deceased":"umbes 1295–Surnud","1293–1384":"1293–1384","1343–Female":"1343–Surnud","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","Abt 1295":"umbes 1295","1343":"1343","1384":"1384","1295":"1295","1293":"1293","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1295–Deceased":"noin 1295–Kuollut","1293–1384":"1293–1384","1343–Female":"1343–Kuollut","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","Abt 1295":"noin 1295","1343":"1343","1384":"1384","1295":"1295","1293":"1293","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1295–Deceased":"environ 1295–Décédée","1293–1384":"1293–1384","1343–Female":"1343–Décédée","1295–Female":"1295–Décédée","Abt 1295":"environ 1295","1343":"1343","1384":"1384","1295":"1295","1293":"1293","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Joan est née environ 1295, à Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Henry Pettit en 1322, à Devon, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1295–Deceas